            "text": "Overview Referencing in Ozone 9 helps you compare and contrast audio in your DAW by allowing you to import up to 10 reference tracks, visualize differences in your music with overlaid spectrum metering, and quickly A/B your audio right in the audition panel.\n Accessing Reference Access the Referencing panel by clicking on the Reference button below the I/O meters. Enable/Disable Referencing by clicking Reference\u0026rsquo;s power button.\n REFERENCING REQUIRES A TRACK\nAlthough you can access the Referencing panel, you cannot enable or turn ON Referencing without adding an actual reference track first.\n  Reference Tracks Workspace You can load up to 10 audio files into the Reference panel and interact with your tracks via the Track Tab bar. Ozone 9 supports the file formats outlined in the table below.\n   Supported file formats     wav   aif/aiff   mp3   AAC   FLAC    REFERENCE TRACKS IN OZONE 9 APPLICATION\nWhen using the Reference panel in the Ozone application, the loaded references will be shared across different tracks. Each track in a given Ozone project will display the same 10 reference tracks in the Reference panel.\n Track Tabs Each tab represents an audio file and its associated settings within the current Ozone project. You can navigate the Track tabs using the methods and controls outlined in the table and image below.\n   LABEL TRACK TAB NAVIGATION METHOD DESCRIPTION      Add Tracks Click on the + button next to the empty Reference track tab to select a reference track from your file directory to load into Ozone 9.    Re-ordering Tracks Click and drag track tabs to change the order of tracks in the project.    Removing Tracks Two methods: **1.**Right-click on a track tab and select “Remove Track”. **2.**Click on a tab to select it, then click on the X button. Either method will instantly remove the reference track from Ozone 9.     Controls The Reference Panel includes the following controls:\n Loop Segement Controls Loop Reference Playback Reference Track Audition Reference Gain Select All Reference I/O Metering Options   Loop Segment Controls You can customize, add, and remove loop segements of your Reference track within he waveform display. You can adjust the following controls outlined in the image and table below.\n    LABEL CONTROL DESCRIPTION      Region Selectors Click and drag the Region Selector handles LEFT or RIGHT to set a region of the waveform to be a designated loop segement.    Name Loop Segments Click on the text above the loop segment to bring up a text-field. Enter the desired loop name and either hit Enter/ Return or click outside of the text-field to save the loop segment name.    Insert Loop Right-click on the desired postion of your loop segment on the waveform clip and select “Insert Loop” to insert a Range Selector that defines the loop.    Remove Loop Right-click on a loop segment and select “Remove Loop” to remove one of the Range Selectors that defined the loop.    Region Selectors in Reference Panel\nWhen tracks are initially loaded into the Reference panel, handles will appear overlaid on the waveform display. The handles represent boundaries of predetermined loop points. The loop boundaries are placed based on similar segments detected in the track, this uses the same machine learning technology used to generate the segmentation bar under waveforms in the Ozone application.\n  REFERENCE TRACKS DEFAULT NAMING\nBy default, the segments will be named with a letter. (A/B/C/D/E)\n Loop Reference Playback Click anywhere within a loop segment and hit the Spacebar to loop reference playback on a specific segment.\nAudition Reference Enable playback of the actively selected reference track by clicking the power button next to the Reference panel button.\nGain Adjust the reference track output gain using the Gain slider.\nSelect All Enable to loop the entire reference track.\nReference I/O Metering Options The I/O options pop-up menu above the I/O meters contains metering options for Reference tracks.\n    REFERENCE METER OPTION DESCRIPTION     Replace Input with Reference When enabled, the Ozone input meter will display the reference track level.   Show Reference Spectrum When enabled, the Reference track spectrum will be displayed in the module spectrum meters alongside the spectrum meter of your current track.",
